<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/170: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Maginnis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-27T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 27,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>3. Your January 25, 10 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Cable Department whether, in your opinion, disturbances are likely to
                            occur which would prove embarrassing to the United States if the
                            Government of Bolivia were accorded formal recognition after the
                            inauguration of Saavedra. Will the convention continue to function as a
                            congress for the constitutional period, or will new general elections be
                            held next May?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>